      <para styleclass="Heading1">Database</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Most Database commands are implemented as User Defined command in the standard header files, and call Runtime Functions under the hood.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Make sure that you include the standard header file during compilation (so do NOT use the option <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="opt-nostddefs">-nostddefs</link>). </para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">If you use the compiler option <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="opt-stddefs">-stddefs</link> to use an alternate standard header file then it is your responsibilty to make sure that these commands are implemented.</para>
